FuncDef: The cut access-user nat-ip-address command enables a CGN device to log out users based on public IP addresses.

ParaDef.Info:
Specifies the IP address of a user to be logged out.
The value is in dotted decimal notation.

Specifies the end IP address of a user to be logged out.
The value is in dotted decimal notation.

Specifies the name of a VPN instance to which a user to be logged out belongs.
The value is a string of 1 to 31 case-sensitive characters, spaces not supported. When double quotation marks are used around the string, spaces are allowed in the string.

ExtraInfo:
Usage Scenario
If a VSUF-80/VSUF-160/VSUI-160-E/VSUI-400/VSUI-400-E/VSUI-400A/VSUI-400A-E/VSUI-400-S/VSUI-400A-S fails, CGN users cannot access the Internet using private IP addresses. To address this problem, CGN users are allowed to access the Internet using public IP addresses. After the VSUF-80/VSUF-160/VSUI-160-E/VSUI-400/VSUI-400-E/VSUI-400A/VSUI-400A-E/VSUI-400-S/VSUI-400A-S is restored, the CGN public network users can be logged out and access the Internet again using private IP addresses. By default, a manual user cutback is performed. To enable the automatic user cutback function, run the cut access-user nat-ip-address command to log out users based on public IP addresses.
Precautions
In VS mode, this command is supported only by the admin VS.
